<taxonomicName id="42854D72FFF3FFB7723A0CB679E9FE16" baseAuthorityName="Spitz" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[829,990,474,495]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Sophista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifasciata">
<emphasis id="B7F1EAE3FFF3FFB7723A0CB679E9FE16" box="[829,990,474,495]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="534">S. latifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the narrow white band on DW. Left valva with harpe approximately three times longer than wide; harpe and ampulla with dentate margin and without internal spines; ampulla curved inwards. Right valva with harpe approximately two times longer than wide; harpe with median 
<emphasis id="B7F1EAE3FFF3FFB775F60F1E7ECAFD71" box="[1265,1277,626,648]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="534">–</emphasis>
dorsal spinous projection, curved inwards. Distal portion of aedeagus lanceolate and dorsally dilated at apical third.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="853A36F1FFF3FFB7723A0F817E05FCFB" blockId="8.[829,1444,749,1076]" box="[829,1074,749,770]" pageId="8" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis id="B7F1EAE3FFF3FFB7723A0F817E05FCFB" box="[829,1074,749,770]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="534">Taxonomic comments</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CD9F657AFFF3FFB7723A0E677F7DFBCA" pageId="8" pageNumber="534" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="853A36F1FFF3FFB7723A0E677E5FFC62" blockId="8.[829,1444,749,1076]" pageId="8" pageNumber="534">
<taxonomicName id="42854D72FFF3FFB7723A0E6779DDFCD8" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Zacca &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1953" box="[829,1002,779,801]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Sophista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matto" status="stat. nov.">
<emphasis id="B7F1EAE3FFF3FFB7723A0E6779DDFCD8" box="[829,1002,779,801]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="534">Sophista matto</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ACC25798FFF3FFB772F40E677E69FCD9" box="[1011,1118,779,800]" pageId="8" pageNumber="534">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="42854D72FFF3FFB774340E677942FCC6" baseAuthorityName="Spitz" baseAuthorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Sophista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifasciata">
<emphasis id="B7F1EAE3FFF3FFB774340E677942FCC6" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="534">S. latifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and indeed was originally described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="42854D72FFF3FFB772B30E257F37FCA7" authority="(Evans, 1953)" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1953" box="[948,1280,840,862]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Sophista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifasciata">
<emphasis id="B7F1EAE3FFF3FFB772B30E257E62FCA4" box="[948,1109,840,862]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="534">S. latifasciata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E1144B00FFF3FFB775600E247ECFFCA7" author="Evans WH" box="[1127,1272,840,862]" pageId="8" pageNumber="534" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref11490" refString="Evans WH. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. London: British Museum (Natural History). v + 246 pp., pls. 26 - 53." type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans, 1953</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Despite their superficial resemblance, the two species have very distinctive male genitalia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="853A36F1FFF3FFB772510EC87F7DFBCA" blockId="8.[829,1444,749,1076]" pageId="8" pageNumber="534">
<materialsCitation id="35ED3CACFFF3FFB772510EC87F03FBCD" collectionCode="NHMUK" collectorName="Hamilton Druce &amp; J. J. Joicey" country="Brazil" location="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="534" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
The 
<typeStatus id="5A3E8853FFF3FFB772970EC879C7FC43" box="[912,1008,932,954]" pageId="8" pageNumber="534">holotype</typeStatus>
male is deposited in the 
<collectionCode id="E394AE34FFF3FFB774310EC87F97FC40" box="[1334,1440,932,953]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" name="Natural History Museum, London" pageId="8" pageNumber="534" type="Museum">NHMUK</collectionCode>
, with the following labels (separated by slashes): / Cuyaba Matto Grosso, 
<collectingCountry id="FD927661FFF3FFB775670E8D7E92FC0E" box="[1120,1189,993,1015]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="534">Brazil</collectingCountry>
/ ex. coll. 
<collectorName id="28705327FFF3FFB7743F0E8D79B5FBEC" pageId="8" pageNumber="534">Hamilton Druce</collectorName>
1919 / 
<collectorName id="28705327FFF3FFB772E6096C7E6EFBEC" box="[993,1113,1023,1045]" pageId="8" pageNumber="534">J.J. Joicey</collectorName>
coll. B.M. 1925-451 / [label with the male genitalia dissected by Evans]
</materialsCitation>
/.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
